data.description: First time on the market! The beautiful home was lovingly built by the current owners and is waiting for you to come make it yours before the holidays. The welcoming entry way leads to both the family sitting area off the kitchen and to the living room. In the oversized sunken in living room you will enjoy expansive views of the entire valley, from the ocean, across the bay to Eureka, to the mountains. The large fireplace is a central focal point adding warmth, coziness and a great hang out. The kitchen is large, welcoming, and updated with room for multiple cooks or guest to lend a helping hand. The double ovens and expansive counter space is ready for you to create a holiday feas The kitchen is flanked by a formal dining area that also enjoys views of the valley, and a cozy sittingarea with it's own pellet stove. The large sliding door to the back yard nestled between the kitchen and sitting area makes entertaining a breeze. Downstairs you will find a full bar/entertainment room with its own half bath. The ceiling has been sound proofed with cork, giving the ability to turn it into a movie room or a great all night hang out while the upstairs occupants can rest. Upstairs the large primary bedroom with impressively sized on-suit also takes full advantage of the beautiful views. Needing two closets? The primary bedroom has it. Also upstairs is the guest bath and two additional bedrooms. The more than an acre lot leaves room for multiple gardens, outdoor recreation and expansion. Call your favorite agent today for a private showing of this first time on the market home.
